{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de105-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9105"},"text":"§ 9105.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Audits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de106-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de107-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The financial statements of Government corporations shall be audited by the Inspector General of the corporation appointed under chapter 4 of title 5, or under other Federal law, or by an independent external auditor, as determined by the Inspector General or, if there is no Inspector General, by the head of the corporation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de108-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Audits under this section shall be conducted in accordance with applicable generally accepted government auditing standards.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de109-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Upon completion of the audit required by this subsection, the person who audits the statement shall submit a report on the audit to the head of the Government corporation, to the Chairman of the Committee on Government Operations of the House of Representatives, and to the Chairman of the Committee on Governmental Affairs of the Senate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de10a-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Comptroller General of the United States—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de10b-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" may review any audit of a financial statement conducted under this subsection by an Inspector General or an external auditor;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de10c-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shall report to the Congress, the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, and the head of the Government corporation which prepared the statement, regarding the results of the review and make any recommendation the Comptroller General of the United States considers appropriate; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de10d-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/4/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" may audit a financial statement of a Government corporation at the discretion of the Comptroller General or at the request of a committee of the Congress.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"An audit the Comptroller General performs under this paragraph shall be in lieu of the audit otherwise required by paragraph (1) of this subsection. Prior to performing such audit, the Comptroller General shall consult with the Inspector General of the agency which prepared the statement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de10e-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A Government corporation shall reimburse the Comptroller General of the United States for the full cost of any audit conducted by the Comptroller General under this subsection, as determined by the Comptroller General. All reimbursements received under this paragraph by the Comptroller General of the United States shall be deposited in the Treasury as miscellaneous receipts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de10f-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Upon request of the Comptroller General of the United States, a Government corporation shall provide to the Comptroller General of the United States all books, accounts, financial records, reports, files, workpapers, and property belonging to or in use by the Government corporation and its auditor that the Comptroller General of the United States considers necessary to the performance of any audit or review under this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de110-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9105/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Activities of the Comptroller General of the United States under this section are in lieu of any audit of the financial transactions of a Government corporation that the Comptroller General is required to make under any other law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbd8de111-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1043"},"text":"96 Stat. 1043","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/86/tIV/s403"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–86, title IV, § 403","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/609"},"text":"101 Stat. 609","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/233/tVII/s703"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–233, title VII, § 703","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1706"},"text":"101 Stat. 1706","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/399/tVI/s602"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–399, title VI, § 602","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-17"},"text":"Aug. 17, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1006"},"text":"102 Stat. 1006","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/tV/s511/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, title V, § 511(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/406"},"text":"103 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/576/tIII/s305"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–576, title III, § 305","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-15"},"text":"Nov. 15, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/2853"},"text":"104 Stat. 2853","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/82/tII/s202/e/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–82, title II, § 202(e)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-09-21"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/888"},"text":"107 Stat. 888","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286/s4/b/58"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286, § 4(b)(58)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4349"},"text":"136 Stat. 4349","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbd8de112-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idbd8de113-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idbd8de114-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:850(1st sentence 1st–16th, 30th–46th words, 4th–last sentences).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1945-12-06/ch557/s105"},"text":"Dec. 6, 1945, ch. 557, § 105","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/59/599"},"text":"59 Stat. 599","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Aug. 30, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/518/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–518, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/698"},"text":"78 Stat. 698","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Jan. 2, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/604/s601/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–604, § 601(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1962"},"text":"88 Stat. 1962","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:857(1st sentence 1st–26th, 39th–last words, 4th–last sentences).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1945-12-06/ch557/s202"},"text":"Dec. 6, 1945, ch. 557, § 202","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/59/600"},"text":"59 Stat. 600","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Aug. 30, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/518/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–518, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/698"},"text":"78 Stat. 698","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Jan. 2, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/604/s601/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–604, § 601(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1962"},"text":"88 Stat. 1962","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:866(a)(last proviso), (b).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1945-12-06/ch557/s301"},"text":"Dec. 6, 1945, ch. 557, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/59/601"},"text":"59 Stat. 601","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:850(1st sentence 17th–29th words, 2d, 3d sentences).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:857(1st sentence 27th–38th words, 2d, 3d sentences).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(d)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:850(1st sentence proviso).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(e)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:866(a)(words before 1st comma, 1st proviso), (d).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(f)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:866(c).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"9105(g)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:866(a)(words between 1st comma and 1st proviso).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the section, the words “Comptroller General” are substituted for “General Accounting Office” for consistency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “rules and . . . of the United States” are omitted as surplus. The words “United States” are added for consistency. The text of 31:850(4th sentence) and 857(4th sentence) and the words “Effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as executed."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(1), the words “pursuant to law” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(2), the words “may make a contract” are substituted for “is authorized in his discretion to employ by contract” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), before clause (1), the words “at the place or places” and “of the respective corporations” are omitted as surplus. The words “A Government corporation shall” are added for clarity. In clause (1), the words “make available . . . for audit all records” are substituted for “The representatives of . . . shall have access to all books, accounts, financial records, reports, files, and all other papers” for consistency and because of the restatement. The words “things, or” are omitted because they are included in “property”. In clause (2), the word “full” is omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (d) is substituted for 31:850(1st sentence proviso words before 7th comma) because of the restatement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the words “The Comptroller General shall pay the cost of an audit” are substituted for “The expenses of auditing the financial transactions of wholly owned and mixed-ownership Government corporations as provided in sections 850 and 857 of this title shall be borne out of appropriations to the General Accounting Office” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “full” and “otherwise . . . funds of any . . . be used to . . . of the offices” are omitted as surplus. The words “except the cost of such audits contracted for and undertaken prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1945-04-25"},"text":"April 25, 1945","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as executed."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (g) is substituted for 31:866(a)(words between 1st comma and 1st proviso) for clarity and consistency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbd8de115-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbd8de116-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":" substituted “chapter 4 of title 5,” for “the Inspector General Act of 1978 (5 U.S.C. App.),”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/82"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–82","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, or under other Federal law,” before “or by an independent”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/576"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–576","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section required Comptroller General to audit financial transactions of Government corporations at least once every 3 years, the Federal Savings and Loan Insurance Corporation and Federal home loan banks each year, the Federal Asset Disposition Association and the Federal Agricultural Mortgage Corporation as necessary; suggested that Comptroller General in conducting an audit use reports of examinations of Government corporation by supervising administrative agency and authorized Comptroller General to contract for professional services; required audits to be conducted consistent with principles and procedures applicable to commercial corporate transactions; set forth responsibility for payment of audit cost, and authorized appropriations."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73","children":[],"tail":" struck out “Federal Savings and Loan Insurance Corporation and” after “The Comptroller General shall audit the” and inserted sentence at end requiring the Comptroller General to audit the Resolution Funding Corporation annually."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/399"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–399","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Corporation” for “Association” in subpar. (B)(i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/233"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–233","children":[],"tail":" added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/86"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–86","children":[],"tail":" added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbd8de117-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idbd8de118-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Committee on Governmental Affairs of Senate changed to Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of Senate, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2005","children":[],"tail":", by Senate Resolution No. 445, One Hundred Eighth Congress, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 2004","children":[]